I might understand to help maybe with 20% since if it is an enclosed stadium you can enjoy more, but 2/3 when they are the 9th richest owners? SoFi was 100% privately funded in California. Cheers to the writer of this article for bringing this to the public who might not understand finances well. 

Edit: Most viral I knew you all liked sportsball! I am happy for the people who get the new stadium, my hope is that taxes are not raised significantly. Our taxes around Chicago are high enough and wouldn't want a property tax or sales tax increase.
